Alexandra Bush

Bio

Historical

Biography

2011-12 HIGHLIGHTS:

Appeared in nine tournaments…Ranked third on the Wildcats, averaging 81.8 strokes per round…Posted three top 10 finishes and five top 30 efforts…Shot 83-77-160 to finish seventh at the Saint Martin’s Invitational Oct. 7-8…Placed seventh with a 79-80-159 at the Cal State East Bay Pioneer Shootout Mar. 2-4…Matched her career-best round of 75 on the way to a 10th place finish in the Sonoma State Invitational Oct. 24-25.

2010-11 HIGHLIGHTS:

Ranked fourth on the Wildcats with an average of 84.3 strokes per round…Posted three top 30 finishes…Placed 23rd at the Oct. 18-19 Lady Otter Invitational…Shot a career-best 75 Apr. 5 during the final round of the Grand Canyon Spring Invitational.

2009-10 HIGHLIGHTS:

Appeared in three tournaments as a freshman, notching a pair of top 40 finishes…Averaged 85.3 strokes a round.

AMATEUR HIGHLIGHTS:

Finished 32nd (79-76-79-234) at the 2011 California Women’s Championship July 18-20 in Temecula…CIF Indivdiualist in 2008…Won the Santa Margarita Catholic High School Coach’s Award in 2007…Earned student-athlete honors in 2005 and 2007.

PERSONAL:

Born 3/31/91 in Yorba Linda…Daughter of George and Allison…Has three younger siblings: Katy, Clark and Curtis…Biggest sports thrill was a hole-in-one in 2006…Volunteered over the summer at Friends for Life in Orlando, FL…Says the best things about Chico are the fall season and restaurants…Best advice ever received: “keep calm, carry on”…Always plays with her hair braided and with a blue line on her golf ball…Would skydive and travel around the world if money were no object…Psychology major.
